query:
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS `external_economic_factors` (
  `id` int AUTO_INCREMENT NOT NULL,
  `month` int NOT NULL,
  `year` int NOT NULL,
  `unemployment_rate` int,
  `economic_growth_rate` int,
  `inflation_rate` int,
  `labor_force_participation_rate` int,
  `average_wage_growth` int,
  `industry_growth_index` int,
  `job_openings_index` int,
  `consumer_confidence_index` int,
  `notes` text,
  `data_source` varchar(255),
  `createdAt` timestamp NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  `updatedAt` timestamp NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  CONSTRAINT `external_economic_factors_id` PRIMARY KEY(`id`)
)
